about.summary: An Analysis Tool for Gridded and Non-Gridded Data.

name: pyferret
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "7.0" %}
{% set commit = "67aed0fa29f2d3f28e624030d746d23d146fc387" %}

package:
    name: pyferret
    version: {{ version }}

source:
    fn: pyferret-{{ version }}-{{ commit }}.tar.bz2
    url: https://github.com/NOAA-PMEL/PyFerret/archive/{{ commit }}.tar.gz
    sha256: f02537b14371a8adcfe02c55701e6c57eb9b4fb0f65f7f2be49e920f707cbf0b
    patches:
        - site_specific.patch

build:
    number: 3
    skip: True  # [win or py3k or osx]

requirements:
    build:
        - python
        - netcdf-fortran 4.4.*
        - numpy x.x
        - cairo
        - pango
        - gcc
    run:
        - netcdf-fortran 4.4.*
        - numpy x.x
        - cairo
        - pango
        - pyqt
        - libgcc

test:
    imports:
        - pyferret

about:
    home: http://ferret.pmel.noaa.gov/Ferret
    license: MIT
    summary: 'An Analysis Tool for Gridded and Non-Gridded Data.'

extra:
    recipe-maintainers:
        - eugeneburger
        - karlmsmith
        - ocefpaf
